0.user_question: James runs 12 miles a day for 5 days a week.  If he runs 10 miles an hour how many hours does he run a week?

direct_answer.text: To calculate this problem we need to find out firstly James’ running distance per week which equals (Miles/Day)×(Days/Week)=(12 Miles/Day) × (5 Days/Week)=60miles/week .Now divide these resultant weeks by speed ,Hours= Distance/Speed=(60 Mile)/(10 mph)=6 Hours.
